## Final output

### Files changed
- `proofs/lean/extraction/While_count_upObligations.lean` ‚Äî replaced the single `sorry` on `count_up_while_postcondition` with a full proof following the canonical two-stage `while`-loop pattern from `proof_patterns/while_example/README.md` and `gcd_while_modified`. The other two theorems (`count_up_while_zero`, `count_up_while_total`) were already term-level corollaries of the postcondition and now type-check.

### Proof structure (added)
- **Loop infrastructure** ‚Äî `countInv n i := i.toNat ‚â§ n.toNat`, `countTerm n i := n.toNat - i.toNat`, and abbreviations `countCond`, `countBody`, `countLoop` that mirror the extracted definition so `dsimp` triggers defeq with the extracted `rust_primitives.hax.while_loop`.
- **Stage 1 ‚Äî `count_loop_triple`**: Hoare triple on `Loop.MonoLoopCombinator.while_loop` via `Std.Do.Spec.MonoLoopCombinator.while_loop`. The body step shows (a) `i + 1` doesn't overflow `u64` (using `i < n ‚â§ 2^64 ‚àí 1`), (b) the termination measure strictly decreases, (c) the invariant `(i + 1).toNat ‚â§ n.toNat` is preserved.
- **Stage 2 ‚Äî `count_function_triple`**: strengthen post (from `countInv n r ‚àß ¬¨cond r` derive `r = n` since `r ‚â§ n` and `n ‚â§ r`); weaken pre (`True ‚Üí countInv n 0`); reformulate the function body via `unfold` + `bind_pure`.
- **Stage 3 ‚Äî `count_up_while_postcondition`**: convert the Hoare triple to the equation `f n = RustM.ok n` via `RustM.Triple_iff_BitVec`, with the standard case-split on the `RustM` constructors (`none` / `ok` / `error`).

### Sub-goals that needed care
